The paper deals with distributed computation and algorithms, which suggests that it belongs to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The concept of network decomposition is a graph theory topic, which suggests that it belongs to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which suggests that it belongs to cs.AL (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper addresses the minimum dominating set problem, which is a well-studied problem in distributed computing, suggesting that it belongs to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
